"/scouterLookup": Handles the request for the scouters of a specific match
    Input: json of type MatchInfoRequest (json_parser.go 124)
        Body:
            {
                "Match": 0,
                "isBlue": false,
                "DriverStation": 0
            }
    Output: A list of the names of the scouters in plain text separated by a comma

"/userInfo": Fetches informtation about a user from a username. Updates an SQL table about accolades if uuid is supplied.
    Input:
        Header:
            username: the username of the user you want to request
            uuid: must belong to the username for it to be used. will be ignored otherwise
    Output: UserInfo in json format
        {
            "Username": "",
            "DisplayName": "",
            "Accolades": null,
            "Badges": [
                {
                    "ID": "",
                    "Description": ""
                },
            ],
            "Score": 0,
            "LifeScore": 0,
            "HighScore": 0,
            "Color": 0,
            "Pfp": ""
        }

"/certificateValid": Checks if a certificate if is valid
    Input:
        Header:
            Certificate
    Output: A status code 200 on success, 500 for invalid

"/getPfp": Fetches the default profile picture or the pfp of the specified user
    Input:
        Header:
            username: username of user
    Output: the entire image file of the profile picture stored locally. most likely in jpg and png. not specified

